Key Match Events: Gunnar Henderson hit a two-run home run in the second inning
Grayson Rodriguez pitched eight outstanding innings with seven strikeouts and no walks
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Orioles secured a potentially crucial tiebreaker in the AL East with an 8-0 victory over the Rays
Others: The Orioles extended their streak to 87 consecutive series of at least two decisions without being swept
The Rays' bullpen allowed two runs in the fifth inning, snapping a streak of four or fewer earned runs allowed in 11 consecutive games
